doctors.name: Dr. Jaehon Kim
doctors.bio: Dr. Jaehon Kim is a board-certified orthopedic surgeon specializing in hand and wrist surgery. He completed his fellowship in Hand and Microvascular Surgery at NYU and has extensive experience treating complex upper extremity fractures, including broken arms, wrist fractures, and hand injuries. Dr. Kim is known for his minimally invasive surgical techniques and patient-centered approach to care.

reviews.author: Sarah M.
reviews.text: Dr. Kim treated my broken wrist after a fall. He was incredibly thorough in explaining my treatment options and the surgery went perfectly. Six weeks later, I have full range of motion and no pain. Highly recommend!

reviews.author: Michael T.
reviews.text: Broke my arm playing basketball and Dr. Kim performed the surgery. He was professional, explained everything clearly, and followed up personally. The healing process was smooth and I'm back to playing sports.

reviews.author: Jennifer L.
reviews.text: Dr. Kim is an exceptional surgeon. He fixed my complex wrist fracture with plates and screws. His bedside manner is excellent and he took time to answer all my questions. The scar is minimal and I've regained full function.

reviews.author: David R.
reviews.text: Very knowledgeable and skilled surgeon. My radius fracture healed well under his care. Only minor complaint is the wait times can be long, but worth it for his expertise.

doctors.name: Dr. Michael Hausman
doctors.bio: Dr. Michael Hausman is a renowned orthopedic surgeon with over 45 years of experience in hand and upper extremity surgery. He is a Professor of Orthopedic Surgery at the Icahn School of Medicine and has published over 150 peer-reviewed articles. Dr. Hausman specializes in complex fracture reconstruction, wrist arthroscopy, and revision surgery for failed previous treatments. He is recognized nationally as a leader in hand and wrist trauma care.

reviews.author: Patricia W.
reviews.text: Dr. Hausman is a legend in his field. He repaired my badly broken arm that another surgeon said was too complex. His experience shows in every aspect of care. I'm forever grateful.

reviews.author: Robert K.
reviews.text: After a severe car accident, Dr. Hausman reconstructed my shattered wrist. His surgical skill is extraordinary. A year later, I have nearly full function restored. Cannot recommend him enough.

reviews.author: Maria G.
reviews.text: Saw Dr. Hausman for a second opinion on my arm fracture. His decades of experience were evident. He performed a complex procedure that saved my ability to use my hand. Truly a master surgeon.

reviews.author: James H.
reviews.text: Highly skilled and experienced. Fixed my nonunion fracture that wasn't healing properly. Very professional though his schedule is quite busy so appointments can take time to get.

doctors.name: Dr. Benjamin Rosenstadt
doctors.bio: Dr. Benjamin Rosenstadt is a board-certified orthopedic surgeon specializing in hand and upper extremity surgery. He completed his hand surgery fellowship at the University of Pennsylvania and has particular expertise in treating sports-related hand and wrist injuries, fractures, and ligament injuries. Dr. Rosenstadt is known for his innovative approaches to fracture fixation and his commitment to getting patients back to their activities quickly and safely.

reviews.author: Emily S.
reviews.text: Dr. Rosenstadt treated my broken hand from a cycling accident. He was compassionate, explained all options clearly, and the surgery was a success. Very happy with the results and minimal scarring.

reviews.author: Andrew B.
reviews.text: Excellent doctor! Broke my arm skiing and Dr. Rosenstadt got me back on the slopes in 8 weeks. His surgical technique is top-notch and he really cares about his patients' recovery.

reviews.author: Lisa M.
reviews.text: Very good surgeon who fixed my wrist fracture. Professional and thorough. Follow-up care was excellent. Only wish the office staff was a bit more responsive with scheduling.

reviews.author: Kevin P.
reviews.text: Dr. Rosenstadt is fantastic. He performed surgery on my broken radius and ulna. Explained everything in detail and checked on me personally after surgery. Couldn't ask for better care.

doctors.name: Dr. Paul Cagle
doctors.bio: Dr. Paul Cagle Jr. is a board-certified orthopedic surgeon and Assistant Professor at Mount Sinai, specializing in shoulder and elbow surgery. He completed his fellowship in Shoulder and Elbow Surgery at the Hospital for Special Surgery. Dr. Cagle has expertise in treating upper arm fractures, elbow trauma, rotator cuff injuries, and complex shoulder reconstructions. He is actively involved in clinical research and has published numerous studies on shoulder and elbow outcomes.

reviews.author: Thomas J.
reviews.text: Dr. Cagle repaired my broken humerus after a fall. His expertise in shoulder and elbow surgery is exceptional. The surgery went perfectly and physical therapy is going well. Very pleased with the outcome.

reviews.author: Rachel K.
reviews.text: Broke my elbow in a car accident and Dr. Cagle performed reconstruction surgery. He's incredibly skilled and has a great bedside manner. Took time to explain the procedure and recovery process thoroughly.

reviews.author: Daniel W.
reviews.text: Outstanding surgeon. Dr. Cagle fixed my fractured shoulder and I'm amazed at the recovery. He's knowledgeable, patient, and truly cares about getting you back to normal function.

reviews.author: Michelle F.
reviews.text: Very good experience with Dr. Cagle. He treated my upper arm fracture with surgery and the results are excellent. Professional and thorough. Would definitely recommend.

doctors.name: Dr. David Forsh
doctors.bio: Dr. David Forsh is a fellowship-trained orthopedic trauma surgeon specializing in complex fracture care and polytrauma. He completed his trauma fellowship at the R Adams Cowley Shock Trauma Center at the University of Maryland. Dr. Forsh has extensive experience treating severe fractures, nonunions, malunions, and pelvic trauma. He is particularly skilled in managing multiple traumatic injuries and complex reconstructive procedures. Dr. Forsh is also experienced in pediatric trauma care.

reviews.author: Christopher M.
reviews.text: Dr. Forsh saved my life and my mobility after a motorcycle accident. Multiple fractures including my arm and pelvis. His skill in trauma surgery is unmatched. Forever grateful to him and his team.

reviews.author: Amanda L.
reviews.text: After a serious fall, I had multiple broken bones including my arm. Dr. Forsh coordinated my entire care and performed several surgeries. He's an exceptional trauma surgeon who truly cares about his patients.

reviews.author: Mark S.
reviews.text: Dr. Forsh treated my complex arm fracture that wasn't healing properly from a previous surgery elsewhere. He performed a revision surgery with bone grafting and the results are fantastic. Top-tier surgeon.

reviews.author: Susan D.
reviews.text: Excellent trauma surgeon. Dr. Forsh fixed my compound arm fracture after a construction accident. Very skilled and experienced with complex cases. Recovery is going well.
